==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fertilize
<hw>Fer"ti*lize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Fertilized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Fertilizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>fertiliser</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make fertile or
enrich; to supply with nourishment for plants; to make fruitful or
productive; <as>as, to <ex>fertilize</ex> land, soil, ground, and
meadows</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>fertilize</qex> the field that each pretends to gain.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To fecundate; <as>as, to <ex>fertilize</ex>
flower</as>.</def> <rj><au>A. R. Wallace.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fertilized</ent>⟦br⟧
